---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Anton Lenev — programmer, narrator, cosplayer from Rybinsk"
  description="Biography of Anton Lenev: programmer and CTO at Viewst Inc, audiobook narrator on Litres, host of the «Cosplay and Other Things» podcast, cosplayer. Rybinsk, Russia."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    'itemListElement': [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', 'position': 1, 'name': 'Home', 'item': 'https://alenev.ru/en/' },
      { '@type': 'ListItem', 'position': 2, 'name': 'About', 'item': 'https://alenev.ru/en/about/' }
    ]
  })} />

  <article class="about">
    <h1>About Anton Lenev</h1>

    <section class="lead">
      <p>
        Anton Lenev is a programmer, cosplayer, audiobook narrator and podcast host based in Rybinsk, Russia.
        He has combined a software engineering career with creative work for more than a decade — building
        cosplay costumes inspired by games and films, narrating audiobooks for the Litres platform, hosting
        his own podcast, and contributing to technology and pop-culture publications.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="block">
      <h2>Software Engineering</h2>
      <p>
        Anton has worked in IT since 2011. He graduated from the <strong>P.A. Solovyov Rybinsk State Aviation
        Technological Academy</strong> (RGATA) with a software-engineering background. Today he serves as
        <strong>CTO and Frontend Developer at Viewst Inc</strong>, leading the company's technical direction
        and frontend product work.
      </p>
      <p>
        Personal projects include <a href="https://owleye.space/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OwlEye</a> —
        a smart owl-shaped pendant that helps visually impaired people navigate indoor spaces. The project has
        been featured on Habr, Instructables, and in Russian regional media. Another project is
        <a href="https://vk.com/skull_pin" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Skull Pin</a>, a brand of 3D-printed
        hair jewelry.
      </p>
      <p>
        Anton speaks at industry conferences, including <em>SPB Frontend</em> and mobile-development meetups.
        <a href="/en/it">More about projects and talks →</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="block">
      <h2>Audiobook Narration</h2>
      <p>
        Anton is a working audiobook narrator — over 12 titles narrated by him are published on
        <a href="https://www.litres.ru/author/anton-lenev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Litres</a>.
        Genres span fiction and fantasy, classical Russian literature, and non-fiction.
        <a href="/en/audiobooks">Full catalog →</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="block">
      <h2>Podcast</h2>
      <p>
        He hosts <strong>«Cosplay and Other Things»</strong> — a Russian-language podcast about cosplay,
        pop culture, technology and creativity. Episodes are available on Spotify, Apple Podcasts, Yandex Music
        and other platforms. <a href="/en/podcasts">Listen to the podcast →</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="block">
      <h2>Cosplay</h2>
      <p>
        Anton builds cosplay costumes inspired by games and films — Dead Space, Mass Effect, Skyrim, Predator,
        Overwatch, Morozko and more. Materials and techniques include EVA foam, 3D printing, electronics and
        custom lighting. The work has been covered on Habr, Instructables, Tproger, in Igromania, Kanobu, DTF
        and regional Russian outlets. <a href="/en/cosplay">Costume gallery →</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="block">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        The fastest way to reach Anton is via <a href="https://t.me/AntonLenev" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Telegram</a>
        or any of the social profiles in the site footer. Open to collaboration on narration projects, conference
        talks, and media interviews.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>

  <style>
    .about {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      color: var(--color-text);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      display: inline-block;
      background: var(--color-accent);
      padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
      border: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-border);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-offset) var(--shadow-offset) 0 var(--color-border);
    }

    :global([data-theme="dark"]) h1 {
      color: #1a1a1a;
    }

    .lead {
      background: var(--color-surface);
      padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
      border: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-border);
      border-left: 8px solid var(--color-primary);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-offset) var(--shadow-offset) 0 var(--color-border);
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .lead p {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--color-text);
    }

    .block {
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    .block h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      display: inline-block;
      background: var(--color-primary);
      color: white;
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      border: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-border);
      box-shadow: 3px 3px 0 var(--color-border);
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .block p {
      color: var(--color-text);
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .block p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    .block a {
      color: var(--color-primary-dark);
      text-decoration: underline;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .block a:hover { color: var(--color-secondary); }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      h1 { font-size: 1.75rem; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
